  "texts": [
    "If so, then you could use this technology to aid, or at least not interfere with, judicious attention allocation.",
    "This seems perfectly possible.",
    "But certain affordances of recommender systems and the platforms that deploy them raise serious doubts about how easy it is to exercise executive oversight like this.",
    "We focus here on two: (1) like other automated systems, they encourage users to rely on them and make it hard to critically monitor their performance; and (2) they can co-opt and distort moral responsiveness itself.",
    "Together, these affordances not only pose a challenge for exercising the oversight necessary to use recommender systems morally well, they threaten to undermine attentional moral skill altogether."
  ],
